{%- if page.handle == 'our-story' -%}

<!-- ── STORY HERO ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="story-hero">
  <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:radial-gradient(ellipse at 70% 50%,rgba(45,74,64,0.3) 0%,transparent 60%);pointer-events:none;"></div>
  <div style="position:absolute;top:-100px;right:-100px;width:600px;height:600px;background:var(--forest-mist);border-radius:50%;animation:breathe 8s ease-in-out infinite;pointer-events:none;"></div>
  <div class="story-hero-content">
    <div class="section-label" style="color:var(--forest-4);margin-bottom:24px;"><span>British Columbia, Canada</span></div>
    <h1 class="story-hero-heading">
      Built from <em>frustration</em>.<br>Guided by science.
    </h1>
    <p class="story-hero-desc">We got tired of paying for promises. So we built something different: skincare where the ingredients do the talking, not the packaging.</p>
    <div style="margin-top:40px;">
      <a href="{{ routes.all_products_collection_url }}" class="btn-primary">Shop the Collection</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ── STORY BLOCKS ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="story-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="story-block reveal">
      <div class="story-visual" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#e8f4f1,#c8e6df);">
        <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:var(--forest-mist);animation:blobMorph 12s ease-in-out infinite;border-radius:62% 38% 70% 30% / 50% 62% 38% 50%;"></div>
        <span style="position:relative;z-index:2;font-size:72px;">🌿</span>
      </div>
      <div class="story-text-content">
        <div class="story-label">The Beginning</div>
        <h2 class="story-heading">We spent thousands. Our skin never changed.</h2>
        <p class="story-para">Like most Canadians, we tried everything: department store serums, clinical brands, dermatologist recommendations. Some worked a little. Most worked not at all. The patterns became clear: beautiful packaging, impressive claims, and ingredient lists that barely touched clinical effectiveness.</p>
        <p class="story-para">We started asking why. Why does a $200 serum contain 0.1% niacinamide when clinical data shows 10 to 20% is where results actually live? Why do "collagen-boosting" creams not mention that topical collagen molecules are too large to penetrate skin?</p>
        <p class="story-para">The answer, we learned, is that most skincare is built around marketing, not biology.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="story-block reverse reveal">
      <div class="story-visual" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#f5ede0,#e8d5b8);">
        <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:rgba(184,146,74,0.08);animation:blobMorph 14s ease-in-out 2s infinite;border-radius:38% 62% 30% 70% / 62% 38% 62% 38%;"></div>
        <span style="position:relative;z-index:2;font-size:72px;">🔬</span>
      </div>
      <div class="story-text-content">
        <div class="story-label">The Research</div>
        <h2 class="story-heading">So we went to the science instead.</h2>
        <p class="story-para">We spent 18 months in peer-reviewed research before formulating a single product. Dermatology journals, clinical trial data, cosmetic chemistry textbooks. We wanted to understand which ingredients actually work, and at what concentrations.</p>
        <p class="story-para">GHK-Cu (copper peptides) became a focus because the clinical evidence for collagen stimulation is substantial and decades old. Niacinamide at 20% was chosen. Clinical studies show statistically significant pore reduction starting at 10%, so we formulated at twice that concentration. Nothing arbitrary.</p>
        <p class="story-para">We also wanted to understand what does not work, so we could stop including it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="story-block reveal">
      <div class="story-visual" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#e8f5ee,#c8e6d4);">
        <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:rgba(45,74,64,0.06);animation:blobMorph 11s ease-in-out 1s infinite;border-radius:70% 30% 62% 38% / 38% 70% 30% 62%;"></div>
        <span style="position:relative;z-index:2;font-size:72px;">🇨🇦</span>
      </div>
      <div class="story-text-content">
        <div class="story-label">The Mission</div>
        <h2 class="story-heading">Clean formulas. Honest prices. Made for our climate.</h2>
        <p class="story-para">LaLume launched with one guiding principle: every product must justify its existence. No ingredient makes it into a formula without a reason, and that reason must be backed by evidence, not tradition or marketing.</p>
        <p class="story-para">We also priced differently. By skipping department store retail markups and investing in formulas instead of advertising, we can offer clinical-grade actives at prices that do not require a second mortgage.</p>
        <p class="story-para">We are based in British Columbia. We understand Canadian skin: the cold winters, the hard water, the barrier stress of our climate. Everything we make accounts for that.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── VALUES ─────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="values-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="text-align:center;max-width:560px;margin:0 auto 60px;">
      <div class="section-label reveal" style="justify-content:center;">What We Stand For</div>
      <h2 class="section-heading reveal">Four commitments we don't negotiate on.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="values-grid">
      <div class="value-item reveal stagger-1">
        <div class="value-icon">🔬</div>
        <div class="value-title">Ingredient Honesty</div>
        <p class="value-desc">Every ingredient has a published reason for being in the formula. No filler, no greenwashing. If it does not do something meaningful, it does not go in.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="value-item reveal stagger-2">
        <div class="value-icon">💰</div>
        <div class="value-title">Fair Pricing</div>
        <p class="value-desc">Clinical-grade actives should not cost $200. Our margin goes into formula quality, not influencer campaigns or department store shelf space.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="value-item reveal stagger-3">
        <div class="value-icon">🌿</div>
        <div class="value-title">Clean Standards</div>
        <p class="value-desc">No parabens. No sulfates. No synthetic fragrance. No colorants. If it is in a LaLume product, it is there because it helps, not because it is cheap.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="value-item reveal stagger-4">
        <div class="value-icon">🛡️</div>
        <div class="value-title">The Guarantee</div>
        <p class="value-desc">30 days. If you are not visibly happier with your skin, full refund. No receipts, no returns, no questions. We are confident because we formulate confidently.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── CTA ────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section style="background:var(--forest);padding:clamp(80px,10vw,120px) 0;text-align:center;">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="max-width:600px;margin:0 auto;">
      <div class="section-label reveal" style="justify-content:center;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);">Ready to Start?</div>
      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:clamp(32px,4.5vw,54px);font-weight:500;color:#fff;line-height:1.2;letter-spacing:-0.02em;margin-bottom:20px;" class="reveal">Your skin deserves honesty. We will provide it.</h2>
      <p style="font-size:16px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);margin-bottom:40px;line-height:1.7;" class="reveal stagger-1">30-day money-back guarantee. Free shipping to Canada and the US. Full ingredient transparency on every product.</p>
      <div class="reveal stagger-2">
        <a href="{{ routes.all_products_collection_url }}" class="btn-primary" style="background:#fff;color:var(--forest);display:inline-flex;">
          Shop All Products
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
